Introduction

*Basic Definition: style of art that makes use of shapes, textures, colors and forms to create compositions that have limited or no resemblance to features in external reality.

*Examples:

— .class1 #id1 bg:aliceBlue

Current Modes of Observing Abstract Art

*Obtaining your own pieces: items are rare and costly (with some going for as much as $100 million!)

*Going to an art museum: difficult to access if you dont live in a large area, dealing with crowds

*Internet: pieces are scaled down, limited resolution

— .class1 #id1 bg:aliceBlue

The Alternative is Here: Butchie’s Abstract Art Generator!

*Interactive means to produce beautiful works of abstract art via Shiny

*Process is fast and fun: user specifies 3 inputs, presses submit and a masterpiece is generated in seconds

*Each composition is unique

*The app. is totally FREE!

— .class1 #id1 bg:aliceBlue
